<div class="legal-page">

  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: July 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Effective immediately</p>

  <p>
    Kabacu ("we", "us", or "our") is operated by <strong>Creative Time Center (CTC)</strong>. We are committed to protecting your personal information and your right to privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and what rights you have in relation to it.
  </p>
  <p>
    By using our website (<strong>kabacu.com</strong>) and its services — including purchasing data bundles, electronics, automobiles, courses, and using the Kabacu wallet — you agree to the practices described in this policy.
  </p>

  <hr class="divider">

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We collect information you provide directly to us and information generated as you use our platform.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Account information:</strong> Your name (username), email address, country, and password when you register.</li>
    <li><strong>Transaction data:</strong> Records of purchases, wallet top-ups, payment references, and order history.</li>
    <li><strong>Wallet data:</strong> Balances held in your Kabacu wallet (NAIRA, BTT, USDT, Reward Points) and related transaction logs.</li>
    <li><strong>Device and usage data:</strong> IP address, browser type, pages visited, and session duration, collected automatically for security and analytics.</li>
    <li><strong>Communications:</strong> Messages you send to our support team at support@kabacu.com.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To create and manage your Kabacu account.</li>
    <li>To process purchases, wallet top-ups, and course enrolments.</li>
    <li>To send transactional emails — order confirmations, enrolment receipts, and account credentials.</li>
    <li>To provide customer support and respond to enquiries.</li>
    <li>To detect and prevent fraud, unauthorized access, and abuse.</li>
    <li>To improve our platform through aggregated, anonymous analytics.</li>
    <li>To comply with applicable legal obligations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Sharing Your Information</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal data. We share it only in the following limited circumstances:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> We use third-party services such as AWS SES (email delivery) and PalmPay (payment processing). These providers access your data only to perform services on our behalf and are bound by confidentiality agreements.</li>
    <li><strong>CSkillsHub:</strong> When you purchase a course on Kabacu, your registered email is shared with CSkillsHub solely to provision access to the course you enrolled in.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal requirements:</strong> We may disclose information if required to do so by law, court order, or government authority.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Wallet and Payments</h2>
  <p>
    Your Kabacu wallet balance is stored in our database and is linked to your account. All wallet transactions are logged with timestamps and references. We do not store full card details — payment processing is handled by our payment partners. We maintain records of top-up and withdrawal activity for audit and dispute resolution purposes.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We retain your account and transaction data for as long as your account is active and for a period thereafter as required by law or business necessity. You may request deletion of your account at any time by contacting <a href="mailto:support@kabacu.com">support@kabacu.com</a>. Note that transaction records may be retained for legal and accounting purposes even after account deletion.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
  <p>
    We use session cookies to keep you logged in and to protect forms against cross-site request forgery (CSRF). We may use basic analytics cookies to understand platform usage. We do not use third-party advertising cookies. You can disable cookies in your browser settings, but this may affect your ability to use the platform.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Security</h2>
  <p>
    We protect your data using industry-standard measures including HTTPS encryption, hashed password storage (bcrypt), HTTP-only authentication cookies, and CSRF protection on all forms. No method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Kabacu is not directed at children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>You have the right to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access the personal data we hold about you.</li>
    <li>Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
    <li>Request deletion of your account and associated personal data.</li>
    <li>Withdraw consent to marketing communications at any time.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@kabacu.com">support@kabacu.com</a>.</p>

  <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Continued use of Kabacu after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>
    If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:<br>
    <strong>Creative Time Center (CTC)</strong><br>
    Email: <a href="mailto:support@kabacu.com">support@kabacu.com</a>
  </p>

